%% MCP Integration Architecture

%% This diagram details the Data Retrieval Layer of the AutoResolve system. It
%% visualizes the execution of Phase 7, demonstrating how the LangGraph AI agents are
%% strictly decoupled from the target infrastructure's APIs using the Model Context
%% Protocol (MCP). This Client-Server architecture ensures the core AI reasoning loop
%% never contains hardcoded API logic.

%% Key Architectural Mechanisms & Security Boundaries:
%% - The LangGraph Client: Inside the AI worker, the InvestigationNode operates
%%   strictly as an MCP Client. It does not know how to talk to Kubernetes or
%%   Prometheus; it only knows how to ask the MCP servers what tools are available,
%%   injecting the results back into the shared IncidentState memory.
%% - JSON-RPC over Stdio (The Security Airgap): A critical enterprise security tradeoff
%%   is highlighted at the MCP Boundary. Rather than exposing the MCP servers over
%%   REST/HTTP (which would require complex OAuth/JWT overhead), the LangGraph worker
%%   physically spawns the MCP Python scripts as local subprocesses. Communication
%%   occurs entirely over Standard Input/Output (Stdio) via JSON-RPC. This guarantees
%%   an impenetrable boundary with zero exposed network ports.
%% - Dynamic Tool Schema: Upon spawning, the MCP servers dynamically return their
%%   available tool schemas (e.g., query_cpu_metrics, get_pod_logs) as JSON. This
%%   allows the AI (Claude) to autonomously decide which tools to fire without
%%   hardcoded developer intervention.
%% - Agnostic Target Environments: The actual execution of kubectl commands and PromQL
%%   queries is offloaded entirely to the isolated MCP servers. If the target
%%   environment changes (e.g., moving from Prometheus to Datadog), only the MCP server
%%   needs to be updated; the AutoResolve LangGraph brain remains completely untouched.

graph TD
    subgraph AutoResolve_LangGraph_Worker
        State[(IncidentState Memory)]
        IN[InvestigationNode - MCP Client]
        State <-->|Read / Write| IN
    end

    subgraph MCP_Boundary [JSON-RPC over Stdio Protocol]
        IN -->|1. spawn subprocess| K8s[Kubernetes MCP Server]
        IN -->|1. spawn subprocess| Prom[Prometheus MCP Server]
        
        K8s -->|2. return JSON tool schema| IN
        Prom -->|2. return JSON tool schema| IN
    end

    subgraph Target_Environments
        K8s -.->|kubectl / API| K8sCluster[Target K8s Cluster]
        Prom -.->|PromQL| PromServer[Target Prometheus]
    end